summary_text: 1. I met my three friends in college in 1949. 2. We were acquainted as high school athletes. 3. We all attended the same college. 4. I was a farm kid; they were city kids. 5. They enjoyed visiting my farm for hunting. 6. I didn't enjoy hunting, but joined them. 7. After several years, they wanted to hunt bears. 8. Bear hunting in Canada didn't appeal to me. 9. I reluctantly agreed to the bear hunting trip. 10. We flew to Canada and paddled to the location. 11. We backpacked to a rented cabin in the woods. 12. The area was spooky, and we were apprehensive. 13. None of us wanted to hunt bears initially. 14. We spent days playing cards and eating instead. 15. We felt pressure to bring back a bear. 16. We decided to draw cards to choose the hunter. 17. I drew the high card and had to hunt. 18. Reluctantly, I went out with the gun. 19. I encountered a massive bear in the woods. 20. I forgot to load the gun. 21. The bear charged, and I had to run. 22. I yelled for them to open the cabin door. 23. I led the bear into the cabin and shut the door. 24. I told them to handle the bear. 25. My friends thought I fulfilled my commitment. 26. They never invited me to hunt again.

1. I met three friends in 1949 at college. 2. We had known each other from high school athletics. 3. We became good friends at college. 4. I came from a farm; they were city boys. 5. They visited my farm often to hunt. 6. I didn't enjoy hunting much. 7. I joined them to be part of the group. 8. They proposed a bear hunting trip to Canada. 9. I was not excited about bear hunting. 10. They convinced me to join the trip. 11. We flew to Canada and rented canoes. 12. We paddled and hiked to a remote cabin. 13. The woods were intimidating and spooky. 14. We hesitated to hunt after reaching the cabin. 15. We stayed in and played cards for days. 16. We realized we needed a bear to bring home. 17. We decided to draw cards to choose a hunter. 18. I drew the high card against my wishes. 19. I reluctantly went out to hunt a bear. 20. I encountered a bear but forgot to load my gun. 21. The bear chased me back to the cabin. 22. I tricked the bear into the cabin. 23. I shut the door to trap the bear inside. 24. We laughed it off and told the story for years. 25. They didn't invite me hunting again. 26. I lived up to my commitment anyway.
